1.16.20  12:24 am   https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=f_9J86_4Lxo

I have a question about chords in this song, at 2:21:

Is it:

B/F#
Fhalfdim
Gdim
G#m
C#sus9no5
C#9no5
E
Ebaug

     looks pretty good

     I'm not sure about that Fhalfdim one...

     yep, that's a fine choice. might even say B(b5)/F. because there's the feeling that they just dropped that one note down. Doesn't help that the vocal sings another F# here but that's ok

     and unsure about the naming convention for the C#sus9no5->C#9no5.

     for that chord in that context you really don't need to say no 5. the way that is executed in context is perfectly normal

     Because you could call that Badd2/C#->Badd2b5/C#...But you lose the sus, and I'm not sure how much cleaner that is...

     C#9sus4, C#9. totally standard song stuff
